[h1]Installation[/h1]

[h2]Requirements[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Mount & Blade II: Bannerlord v1.3.13[/b]
[*][b][url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2859232415]Bannerlord.Harmony[/url] v2.4.2+[/b] (Required dependency)
[/list]

[h2]Quick Start[/h2]
[list=1]
[*]Subscribe to this mod and Bannerlord.Harmony
[*]Enable in launcher: [b]Harmony, Native, SandBoxCore, SandBox, StoryMode, CustomBattle, Enlisted[/b]
[*]Start/load game, talk to any lord, choose enlistment dialog option
[*]Access [b]Enlisted Status[/b] menu as your hub (camp, quartermaster, orders, leave, discharge)
[/list]

════════════════════════════════════════════════

[h1]Updating the Mod[/h1]

[h2]Normal Updates (No Clean Install Required)[/h2]
Steam automatically updates the mod. Most updates are seamless.

[h2]Major Updates (Clean Install Required)[/h2]
When the changelog says [b]"CLEAN INSTALL REQUIRED"[/b], follow these steps:

[b]METHOD 1: Delete Modules Folder (Recommended - Easiest)[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Unsubscribe from Enlisted
[*]Navigate to: [i]<Bannerlord>\Modules\[/i]
[*]Delete the [b]Enlisted[/b] folder
[*]Resubscribe to the mod
[*]Steam will redownload fresh files
[/list]

[b]METHOD 2: Verify Game Files[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Unsubscribe from Enlisted
[*]Right-click Bannerlord in Steam, Properties, Local Files, [b]Verify Integrity of Game Files[/b]
[*]Resubscribe to Enlisted
[/list]

[b]Why Clean Installs?[/b] Steam Workshop doesn't auto-delete removed files. If we delete JSON content files (events, orders, decisions), old files remain and cause conflicts. Clean installs ensure you have the correct file set.

════════════════════════════════════════════════

[h1]Troubleshooting[/h1]

[h2]Automatic Conflict Detection[/h2]
The mod automatically detects conflicts with other mods at startup. Check these logs:

[b]Log Location:[/b] [i]<Bannerlord>\Modules\Enlisted\Debugging\[/i]

[b]Key Files:[/b]
[list]
[*][i]Conflicts-A_*.log[/i] - Mod conflicts, Harmony patch issues, module health
[*][i]Session-A_*.log[/i] - Current session detailed log
[*][i]Current_Session_README.txt[/i] - Quick guide to what to share when reporting issues
[/list]

[h2]Common Issues[/h2]

[b]Mod menu options don't show[/b]
[list]
[*]Confirm Bannerlord.Harmony is enabled and loaded BEFORE Enlisted in launcher
[/list]

[b]Events don't fire / content missing[/b]
[list]
[*]You likely need a clean install. See "Major Updates" section above
[/list]

[b]War Sails features don't work[/b]
[list]
[*]War Sails DLC must be enabled. Check Session log for [i]W-DLC-*[/i] warnings
[/list]

[b]Game feels "stuck" after leaving menu/encounter[/b]
[list]
[*]Share [i]Session-A_*.log[/i] + mod list/load order on GitHub Issues
[/list]

[b]Save won't load / loads into broken state[/b]
[list]
[*]Check for [i]E-SAVELOAD-*[/i] in Session log, then share both Session and Conflicts logs
[/list]

[h2]Reporting Issues[/h2]
When reporting bugs on [url=https://github.com/Arkpointt/Enlisted/issues]GitHub Issues[/url]:
[list=1]
[*]Include error code(s) if visible (e.g., [i][E-CAMPUI-031][/i])
[*]Attach [i]Session-A_*.log[/i] and [i]Conflicts-A_*.log[/i]
[*]List other active mods and load order
[*]Describe exact steps to reproduce
[/list]

